item.title: CS130-lecture-20200902
item.description: Concerning the survey from last class # The differences between an array and a linked list: Access: arrays can access an spot instantly, linked lists need to iterate from the head until they reach the target. Size: arrays are fixed in size, linked lists can become bigger or smaller Stacks can be implemented using a linked list or an array. FILO Queues can be implemented using a linked list or a circular array.
